  <static seed="52" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring95.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{8x^{13}y^{3}-16y^{3}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>8y^{3}\mathopen{}\left(x^{13}-2\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>8y^{3}</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{8x^{13}y^{3}-16y^{3}}={8y^{3}\mathopen{}\left(x^{13}-2\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
